# Cloudflare Pages redirects (https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/)
#
# Vanity install URL: `curl ... https://keyholetui.com/install.sh | sh` follows
# this 302 to the latest GitHub release installer, over HTTPS end to end.
# Integrity does not depend on the fetch path: the installer verifies the
# SHA-256 checksum (and cosign signature) of the downloaded binary, identically
# whether you reach it via this alias or the GitHub URL directly. The asset is
# published by .github/workflows/release.yml (it copies scripts/install.sh ->
# keyhole-installer.sh on every release).
/install.sh   https://github.com/AlexKasapis/Keyhole/releases/latest/download/keyhole-installer.sh   302
/install      https://github.com/AlexKasapis/Keyhole/releases/latest/download/keyhole-installer.sh   302

# Short links to common GitHub destinations.
/releases     https://github.com/AlexKasapis/Keyhole/releases   302
/repo         https://github.com/AlexKasapis/Keyhole            302
/security     https://github.com/AlexKasapis/Keyhole/security/policy   302
